THE ACTION PLAN

1. Formation of a project team: Form a team of individuals with expertise in areas such as information technology, law, finance, marketing and operations to develop the Voting System and run the Election, with the following tasks:
- Define the scope of the Project and the roles and responsibilities of each team member.
- Identify potential team members who have the required skills and experience.
- Invite potential team members to join the Project and explain the scope and objectives of the Project.
- Evaluate the responses and select the individuals who will be part of the team.
- Assign specific tasks to each team member and set deadlines for completion.
- Provide the necessary resources and support to help the team achieve its objectives.
- Regularly assess the progress of the Project and make adjustments as necessary.
- Communicate regularly with other Guilds or Guild members to ensure everyone is on track and has the information they need to complete their tasks.
- Engage with backers and keep them updated on the progress of the Project.
- Meet your funding goal and ensure that the rewards are fulfilled in a timely manner.
- After the campaign is completed, use the funds to support the development of the Voting System, marketing, and outreach efforts.

2. Secure funding: Secure funding to support the development of the Voting System, as well as marketing and outreach efforts to ensure maximum participation from eligible individuals. The Project Team needs to:
- Create a detailed proposal for the Project, including its goals, budget, and timeline.
- Identify and research potential crowdfunding platforms that allow for technology and infrastructure projects.
- Choose a suitable platform and create a campaign page that clearly outlines the details of the Project, its funding goal, and rewards for backers.

3. Develop the Voting System: The Project team shall work on developing the Voting System that will be used for the Election.

4. Marketing: The Project team shall develop a marketing and outreach plan to promote the campaign and reach a large audience. This can include leveraging your personal network, using social media, and utilizing paid advertising options.

5. Launch a public awareness campaign: The Project team shall launch a comprehensive public awareness campaign to inform the general public about the Election and the purpose of the Architects. This campaign should include a mix of digital and traditional marketing methods to reach a wide audience.

6. Hold the Election: Once the Voting System is up and running, the Project team shall hold the Election for a one-calendar-year period.

7. Count and announce the results: The Project team shall conduct a fair and transparent vote count and announce the results of the Election to the public.

8. Form the Office of Architects: Once the results are announced, the Project team shall assist to form the Architects, and provide them with the necessary resources and support to carry out their responsibilities.

9. Continuously monitor and evaluate the system: The Project team shall regularly monitor and evaluate the performance of the Architects to ensure that they are fulfilling their objectives and serving the best interests of the public.
